# Test Plan â€“ E-commerce Web Application

## 1. Objective

The objective of this test plan is to validate the core business functionality of the e-commerce web application and ensure that critical user journeys operate reliably and consistently.

Primary focus is placed on revenue-impacting flows such as authentication, cart management, and checkout completion.

---

## 2. Scope

### In Scope
- User Registration & Login
- Session Management
- Product Browsing & Search
- Product Details Page
- Cart Operations (Add, Update, Remove)
- Checkout Process (Shipping & Order Confirmation)
- Form Validation & Error Handling

### Out of Scope
- Performance & Load Testing
- Security & Penetration Testing
- Real Payment Processing Integration
- Cross-browser testing beyond Chrome

---

## 3. Test Approach

The following testing techniques were applied:

- Functional Testing of end-to-end business flows
- Risk-Based Testing prioritizing checkout and authentication
- Negative Testing for invalid inputs and improper user behavior
- Boundary Value Analysis for form fields
- Exploratory Testing sessions targeting usability and session handling

---

## 4. Environment

- OS: Windows 10
- Browser: Google Chrome (latest stable version)
- Resolution: 1920x1080
- Test Data: Pre-created test users & generated test orders

---

## 5. Risk Assessment

| Risk Area | Business Impact | Priority |
|------------|----------------|----------|
| Checkout Failure | Revenue Loss | High |
| Login Issues | User Frustration / Abandonment | High |
| Cart Calculation Errors | Incorrect Orders | High |
| Inconsistent Validation | Poor UX | Medium |

---

## 6. Entry Criteria

- Application deployed in test environment
- Core requirements defined
- Test data available

---

## 7. Exit Criteria

- All High severity defects documented
- 100% execution of planned test cases
- Test Summary Report delivered
